  full: "Prophet Musa (A.S.) was born in Egypt during the rule of Pharaoh, who oppressed the Children of Israel and ordered the killing of newborn boys. His mother, following Allah’s inspiration, placed him in a basket and set it afloat on the Nile. He was found by Pharaoh’s wife, who raised him as her own.\n\nAs Musa (A.S.) grew, he was granted wisdom and strength. One day, he unintentionally killed an Egyptian while defending an Israelite, and fled to Madyan. There he married and lived for years until Allah called him to prophethood near Mount Sinai. Allah spoke to him directly and gave him miracles, including his staff turning into a serpent and his hand shining brightly.\n\nMusa (A.S.) was commanded to confront Pharaoh and demand the release of the Children of Israel. Despite Pharaoh’s arrogance and magic from his sorcerers, Musa (A.S.) prevailed by Allah’s power. After severe punishments sent upon Egypt, Musa (A.S.) led his people out, and Allah parted the Red Sea for them while drowning Pharaoh and his army.\n\nIn the desert, Musa (A.S.) received the Torah on Mount Sinai, guiding his people with Allah’s laws. However, some of his followers disobeyed by worshipping a golden calf. Musa (A.S.) remained patient, teaching obedience, worship, and reliance upon Allah. His story shows courage, leadership, and trust in Allah against all odds."
